16/03/2010
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Serb Bojan Guduric pleaded not guilty Monday (March 15th) to charges of murdering prominent Croatian publisher and journalist Ivo Pukanic in October 2008. Guduric is charged along with four other suspects. Pukanic, co-owner and editor-in-chief of the weekly Nacional, was killed in a car bombing in downtown Zagreb, along with the newspaper's marketing director, Niko Franjic. Guduric entered his plea at Zagreb's District Court. (HRT, Beta, RTS - 15/03/10)
